dev-tools.description: Tools for the Datagrok developers (TestManager, DevPanel).

sqlite.description: Support for importing and previewing SQLite files.

tutorials.description: Learn and explore Datagrok through interactive tutorials and a demo app

chem.description: Cheminformatics support: import, rendering, sketching, calculation of properties, predictive models, augmentations, multiple analyses.

demo.description: *Demo* is a [package](https://datagrok.ai/help/develop/develop#packages) for the [Datagrok](https://datagrok.ai) platform. It demonstrates the [scripting](https://datagrok.ai/help/compute/scripting) functionality for [Python](https://www.python.org/), [R](https://www.r-project.org/), [Julia](https://julialang.org/), [NodeJS](https://nodejs.org/), [Octave](https://octave.org/).

clinical-case.description: Analysis of the clinical data represented in the [SDTM](https://www.cdisc.org/standards/foundational/sdtm) format.

pubchem-api.description: Integration with the PubChem web service.

peptides.description: Advanced tools for analyzing collections of peptides.

marvin.description: marvin is a [package](https://datagrok.ai/help/develop/develop#packages) for the [Datagrok](https://datagrok.ai) platform.

oligo-batch-calculator.description: Calculates the following oligonucleotide properties: Length, Optical Density, NMoles, Mass, Molecular Weight, Extinction Coefficient (using nearest neighbour method)

drug-bank.description: Molecular similarity and substructure search capabilities in the [DrugBank](https://go.drugbank.com/) [Open Structures](https://go.drugbank.com/releases/latest#open-data) dataset.

api-tests.description: Automated tests for the [Datagrok JS API](https://datagrok.ai/js-api)

multiplot.description: MultiPlot is a [package](https://datagrok.ai/help/develop/develop#packages) for the [Datagrok](https://datagrok.ai) platform. MultiPlot was developed in purpose to provide to user ability to easily create dashboards based on complex data which have common influencing parameter (usually presented as axis X on charts). Common axis X combined with compact form of presenting charts allow user quickly estimate data meaning.

charpy.description: ChaRPy translates viewers into Python or R scripts, executes them and displays the resulting plots.

compute.description: Provides additional analytical and UI blocks for [Datagrok scientific computing](https://datagrok.ai/help/compute/).

chembl.description: Chembl integration, commonly used queries and browser

charts.description: Charts package provides visualizations built using the [ECharts](https://echarts.apache.org/en/index.html) library.

chembl-api.description: Similarity and substructure search in ChEMBL using its API

bio.description: Bioinformatics support (import/export of sequences, conversion, visualization, analysis). [See more](https://github.com/datagrok-ai/public/blob/master/packages/Bio/README.md) for details.

sunburst.description: Sunburst chart for the datagrok platform

enamine-store.description: Integration with Enamine. Allows to search for molecules available in Enamine, and provides contextual information for the current molecule.

chemspace.description: Integration with Chemspace. Allows to search for molecules available in Chemspace, and provides contextual information for the current molecule.

power-grid.description: PowerGrid contains popular spreadsheet extensions, such as [sparklines](#sparklines) and support for [images](#images).

alation.description: Integration with the Alation data catalog.

arrow.description: Provides support for the Parquet and Feather file formats.

helm.description: Provides support for HELM notation (importing, detecting, rendering, conversion).

gis.description: GIS (geographic information system) functionality, such as maps and geocoding.

phylo-tree-viewer.description: *PhyloTreeViewer* is a [Datagrok package](https://datagrok.ai/help/develop/develop#packages) for phylogenetic trees visualization.

chem-draw-sketcher.description: ChemDraw is a [package](https://datagrok.ai/help/develop/develop#packages) for the [Datagrok](https://datagrok.ai) platform.

dendrogram.description: Computation and visualization of hierarchical data clustering. [Learn more](https://github.com/datagrok-ai/public/blob/master/packages/Dendrogram/README.md)

biostructure-viewer.description: Protein viewers: support for multiple file formats, stand-alone viewer, and in-grid viewer.

bioreactors.description: Simulation of controlled fab-arm exchange mechanism

curves.description: Curves provides support for fitted curves (such as dose-response curves), including in-grid rendering, storing charts in cells, interactivity, and automatic fitting.

ketcher-sketcher.description: Adds [Ketcher](https://lifescience.opensource.epam.com/ketcher/index.html) as an optional molecular sketcher.

samples.description: *Samples* contains sample [data connectors](https://datagrok.ai/help/access/databases/connectors/) and demonstrates [scripting](https://datagrok.ai/help/compute/scripting) and [notebooks](https://datagrok.ai/help/compute/jupyter-notebook) functionality.

hit-triage.description: HitTriage helps chemists assess the quality of hits and decide which compounds should make it to the next stage.

file-editors.description: Support for previewing and opening text file formats (PDF, DOCX)

deqs.description: WebAutoSolver tools for solving ODEs in a browser.

diff-studio.description: WebAutoSolver tools for solving ODEs in a browser.
